<p>And the royal is in great company - as fans of the brand include Rosie Huntington Whiteley and Gigi Hadid. </p>

<p>Meghan Markle appeared overwhelmed with excitement at points during her 'backyard chat' with Gloria, 86, which was filmed last month for Makers Women, a women's empowerment platform that will stream the Q&amp;A in full on Wednesday. </p>

<p>However, in a short teaser clip that was posted on social media on Tuesday afternoon, viewers got a glimpse at Meghan and Gloria together, looking totally at east while relaxing in wooden deck chairs in a lush yard.</p>

<p>At one point, the pair are even joined by Meghan's beloved dogs, black Labrador Pula, and rescue beagle Guy, who happily wandered into the camera shot during the chat, and lay down at the Duchess's feet while she continued chatting with Gloria.  </p>

<p>During the conversation, the mother-of-one - who moved back to the US with Prince Harry and their son Archie in January, expressed her joy at being back in her home country. </p>

<p>'Meg, welcome home, I'm so glad that you're home,' Gloria said to the Duchess at the start of the clip, prompting Meghan to respond: 'Thank you. Me too, for so many reasons.' </p>
